-id="19308975"  data-component='slide'><div class="image"><img class="slide-media media-gallery-slide-media" data-src="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/11/52/06/19308975/5/gallery_medium.jpg" data-src-2x="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/11/52/06/19308975/5/gallery_large.jpg" data-src-4x="https://s.hdnux.com/photos/01/11/52/06/19308975/5/gallery_xlarge.jpg"  data-alt-title="" data-resale-link="0" alt="The ruins of Sutro Baths, near the first cave where Kit Hing Hui, “the Phantom of Playland,” lived starting in 1949." /></div><figcaption  style="opacity: 0;"><span class="count">3<span>of</span>3</span><span class="caption">The ruins of Sutro Baths, near the first cave where Kit Hing Hui, “the Phantom of Playland,” lived starting in 1949.</span><span class="credits">Photo: Sean Havey / The Chronicle</span></figcaption></figure>
